7 SECTION 2. The Ballot Title for the proposed Constitutional
8 amendment as set forth in SECTION 1 of this resolution shall be in
9 the following form:
10 BALLOT TITLE
11 Legislative Referendum No. ____ State Question No. ____
12 THE GIST OF THE PROPOSITION IS AS FOLLOWS:
13 This measure amends Section 8C of Article 10 of the Oklahoma
14 Constitution. Increases in fair cash value of homesteads
15 are limited for individual heads of household age sixty-five
16 (65) or older. The increase cannot exceed the fair cash
17 value of the property during the first year in which the
18 owner was age sixty-five (65) years of age or older. This
19 limit applies if the individual head of household meets both
20 the age requirement and an income limit determined by the
21 United States Department of Housing and Urban Development.
22 This measure would eliminate the income limit requirement.
23 The age limit would not change. The person would be
24 required to have occupied the homestead for ten (10) years.

1 A person could be away from the homestead for a period not
2 to exceed three hundred sixty-five (365) days in a ten-year
3 period and still qualify. The limit on increases in fair
4 cash value of homestead property would only apply if the
5 fair cash value of the homestead is Five Hundred Thousand
6 Dollars ($500,000.00) or less. This value would be
7 determined the same way as it is determined for all other
8 purposes in the property tax system.
